						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab in the Māruti temple at Ṭakkaḷige now kept in the house of Mr. W.T. Apte.</hi></p>						

						<p>Tribhuvana[malla] (Bijjala)—A.D. 1164.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1086, Tāraṇa, Mārggasira, Puṇṇami, lunar eclipse,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1164, November 30, Monday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription seems to registers a gift for repairs of, and worship and offerings in a temple, the details being lost. It refers to a feudatory of the king belonging to Beṇṇeva-kula.</p>						

						</summary>
